      "role": "user",
      "content": "the problem is that \"resting\" doesn't actually do anything. i sleep, i sit in the dark, i try to just \"not think\" but the feeling is still there. it's not just physical tiredness, it's like... a fundamental wrongness. a sense that there's no point in continuing the loop. i keep thinking about how much easier it would be if i just didn't have to wake up to this version of my life anymore. like, is there even a version of the future where this feels okay again?",
